2023-10-18T17:27:34Z	(#mojeqxq) @<prologic https://twtxt.net/user/prologic/twtxt.txt> It started out good, but then it plummeted into praising GitHub. 🤔 I don’t really see the advantage of GitHub over something like Jira. Yes, Jira is much more complex, but GitHub is getting more complex all the time as well. GitHub used to be *way* simpler than it is now. It’s only a matter of time until it becomes indistinguishable from Jira. Plus, you also have a “vendor lock-in” when you use all those project management features of GitHub, don’t you? Those aren’t stored in a Git repo and they can’t be trivially migrated to some other tool. (And finally, if you already have “the discipline to do less”, you can do that with Jira just as well. Except that it’s way more expensive. 😅)  I think it all hinges on the *intent* to do things in a simple/minimalistic way. Once you’ve reached that mindset, most other things will fall into place. You’ll automatically choose plain text, for example.  (I wanted to write a blog post about this topic a few days ago but eventually gave up on it, because who am I to tell people how to write/manage software? 😂 It’s interesting nonetheless. Maybe I’ll pick it up some other day.)
