2024-01-09T17:38:32Z	Been rummaging through the basement and look what I found! The very last LS-120 diskette. 🥳  https://movq.de/v/0e60054c57  This was such a cool thing back then. It had the same physical size as a normal 3½" floppy disk but it could store 120 MB. 🤯  And the drive (I had an internal one) could read both types of disks as well, which, from my perspective, was a lot better than the ZIP drive. The ZIP drive was an additional, specialized drive only for those disks.  Sadly, I have neither drive anymore. Only some disks. The LS-120 one is marked as “defective” anyway. RIP. 🪦  Both were pushed out of the market by writable CDs soon after …
