2024-03-17T15:34:10Z	More basement:  I completely forgot that DVD-RAM was a thing once. Found my old disks and they still work. 🤯 The data on them is from 2008, so they’re not *that* old. Still impressive.  The disks are two-sided. On the photo, that particular side of the disk on the left appears to be completely unused. 🤔  And then I read on Wikipedia that DVD-RAMs aren’t produced anymore at all today. Huh.  (I refuse to tag this as “retrocomputing”. Read/write DVDs that you can use just like a harddisk, thanks to UDF, are still “new and fancy” in my book. 😂)  [![](https://movq.de/v/5bdf173e49/.html%2Dindex%2Dthumb%2Ddvdram.jpg.jpg)](https://movq.de/v/5bdf173e49/dvdram.jpg)
