2024-03-23T16:01:04Z	Rainy day.  I was toying with OS/2 when I noticed that my hard disk was getting a bit full. I’m not aware that something like `ncdu` or just `du` exists in OS/2 Warp 4’s *base system* (I’m sure there’s software like that already available, but I was too lazy to search), so I quickly cobbled a little program together that sums up directory sizes. And there you have it, an installation of Carmageddon was lurking on the disk, weighing in at 200 MB. 🥴  [![](https://movq.de/v/57f01ccd46/.html%2Dindex%2Dthumb%2DIMG_7415%2Dsmall.jpg.jpg)](https://movq.de/v/57f01ccd46/IMG_7415%2Dsmall.jpg)  Being able to cross-compile this from Linux still blows my mind.  Anyway, here’s my tool: https://uninformativ.de/git/dusage  Let’s see, this might be a good opportunity to make an OS/2 GUI version of this. 🤔  I’ve never done that and this might be doable (unlike other stuff I’ve recently tried).
